result.name: Kau Kee Chiu Chow Restaurant

reviews.text: Looks normal but taste amazing! Closes at 4am, fantastic option for late night supper in MK area. Surely will visit again
Ordered these perennially great Teochew dishes. All very satisfying. Oyster pancake a tad oily.. but good still. Great place for Teochew food in HK.

The Chiu Chow food is fine, go for things like the blood cake, marinade platter, oyster pancake, congee with Chiu Chow condiments.  
The stir fried items are hardly stir fried, come swimming in water.

Excellent teochew daipaidong dinner @九记潮州打冷餐馆 Kau Kee Chiu Chow Restaurant Mongkok
2 of us went a bit early at 6.35pm, first time here. restaurant looked small (but actually they have upstairs) & empty. there were not many diners at the time, wasn’t sure what to expect but crowd started flowing in & place basically packed by 7pm+. our 2 other friends were a bit loss so came a while after 7pm. and we saw during the time, a continuous stream of locals filling up the restaurant, that they came to ask to share our table, but we said we had 2pax more on the way. 🙂
food was super! every dish was great!
we ordered a pig stomach soup, having had a very good one at lunch earlier at tao heung.it looked not great but in fact it was very tasty, just like what we had at lunch.
i ordered the braised goose 潮州卤鹅. it was tender & tasty…, nice flavourful braise & meat was tender.the mix braises 卤味拼盘 like 8 different items …taste ok not the best dish for me.not really spectacular. in fact the single item braise goose was better. but it was interesting to try goose intestines, birth intestines etc.
the oyster porridge was very good too, very tasty & many, many plump large fresh oysters.it was really good i think. 🙂such a simple dish & so very tasty…
the 2 fried dishes were excellent-best was the celery with squid & beef….小炒王also good..the fried beef with sotong & celery was way above expectation…super wok hae so very flavourful!and the beef, sotong & celery were all excellent.the 小炒王 also very good, much better than the one at 容记小菜王 we had next day..
we read about the chicken blood 鸡红 but forgot to order.my friends saw many tables ordering it so added the dish.it was super tasty, very smooth & very sweet.the stock was very tasty also..
we had salted fish minced pork often so decided to try the steamed minced pork with squid.nice too, squid slight tough so this & braised combo were the 2 dishes that are less great for meit was ok but not that great. salted fish minced pork would have been nicer.the minced pork was not as smooth & tasty as the one i make.excellent dinner 4pax HK$599 👍👍👍 this place sure come back.service by the young girl very bad..the other middleage servers ok

result.name: 九記潮州打冷菜館

reviews.text: 開到零晨3點，食物的份量偏小，味道可以
Decent traditional Hong Kong food.

今天約了朋友晚飯，午餐唯有自己解決。
走著走著不自然走到九記打冷，我記得已有2年沒有吃過了，想著想著就走了進去。
我不假思索便叫了一個潮州炸蠔餅，一個腐乳炒通菜，和一碗白飯。
從前，當想吃打冷，不奇然就會想到九記，可能是因為住在九龍的關係吧，位於旺角的九記的確十分方便。
食物的味道還是那樣，沒有什麼驚喜，但它的份量郤好像貨幣一樣"縮水"了；如果只基於食物、環境及服務質素作為評分標準，其實可能九記是剛及格而已，但我想我吃的是那份感情吧。
豬紅okay
食物中等水平

result.name: 九記潮州打冷菜館（潮州料理）

reviews.text: 環境一般，食物份量很少，味道不很好，有味精。

今天約了朋友晚飯，午餐唯有自己解決。
走著走著不自然走到九記打冷，我記得已有2年沒有吃過了，想著想著就走了進去。
我不假思索便叫了一個潮州炸蠔餅，一個腐乳炒通菜，和一碗白飯。
從前，當想吃打冷，不奇然就會想到九記，可能是因為住在九龍的關係吧，位於旺角的九記的確十分方便。
食物的味道還是那樣，沒有什麼驚喜，但它的份量郤好像貨幣一樣"縮水"了；如果只基於食物、環境及服務質素作為評分標準，其實可能九記是剛及格而已，但我想我吃的是那份感情吧。

價錢比一般潮州食店便宜
但店服務員太少而客人又太多
還要等位
小炒味精較多，但打冷一流。方便就腳。
打冷菜美味地道，價錢合理
